## Memory Discipline
- `CLAUDE.md` (this + per-project): permanent rules only. Recommended: ≤150 lines.
- `STATUS.md` (per-project root): current sprint snapshot. Recommended: ≤50 lines, replace not append.
- `docs/adr/ADR-NNN-slug.md`: architecture decisions — read on demand, never auto-load.
- No other persistent state. No task lists in docs. No status dashboards.

## Hooks (configure in ~/.claude/settings.json or .claude/settings.json)
`pact-check-hook.sh` reads the edited file path from the hook payload and runs the
static gate only for `.pact`/`.repl` files (and only on the edited file) — wiring
`pact-static-check.sh` directly would full-scan the project on every edit of any file.
```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [{
      "matcher": "Edit|Write|MultiEdit",
      "hooks": [{"type": "command", "command": "~/.claude/scripts/pact-check-hook.sh"}]
    }],
    "Stop": [{
      "hooks": [{"type": "command", "command": "~/.claude/scripts/session-end-secrets-scan.sh"}]
    }]
  }
}
```
